{"word":"παχύνω","slug":"παχύνω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>παχύνω</b></el> <el>(πᾰχύ¯νω,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:παχύς'><el>παχύς</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>to thicken, fatten</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to grow fat</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>: <i>to become thick</i>, of the skull, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> <i>to increase</i>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, <el>ὄλβος ἄγαν παχυνθείς</el> <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> also <i>to make gross</i> or <i>stupid</i>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, <b><a href='S:New Testament'>NTest.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}